HEADWORD: Thienone
<hw>Thi"e*none</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Thien</ets>yl
+ ket<ets>one</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A ketone derivative
of thiophene obtained as a white crystalline substance,
<chform>(C4H3S)2.CO</chform>, by the action of aluminum chloride and
carbonyl chloride on thiophene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

